data.name: BirthdayDate
data.value: Your birthday is set on {0}. If this is incorrect, please correct it by using the /setbirthday <DD-MM-YYYY> command. Or if you don't want to set your birthday year, just use the <DD-MM> format. To remove it from the database, use the /removebirthday command.
data.comment: {0} will be replaced with a date (in words)

data.name: BirthdayNotSet
data.value: Your birthday is currently not set. You can set it by using /setbirthday <DD-MM-YYYY> command. If you don't want to set your birthday year, just use the <DD-MM> format.

data.name: BirthdayRemoved
data.value: Your birthday is removed from the database.

data.name: BirthdaySetFailed
data.value: You entered an incorrect date (or format). Please use the command followed by a correct date.

data.name: BirthdaySetSuccessfully
data.value: Your birthday has been successfully added to the database!
